backOutBid(address).details: A 15-minute threshold has been implemented to prevent scams. This ensures that the winner cannot issue a backout transaction at the last moment.If such a transaction were allowed, it could be included after the auction ends, enabling the winner to claim the NFT and withdraw their funds.calls the oracle to transfer the NFT.

params.returnAddressL1: L1 address where the balance is to be sent to.

claim(address).details: No need to keep the returnAddress private by using a confidential input as the bidding addressis public at this point anyway and anyone can track it's actions.

params.returnAddressL1: L1 address where the valuables are to be sent.

params._auctionEndTime: a linux timestamp;  all bids after that timestamp are not considered
params.minimalBiddingAmount: every bid less than that will not be considered
params.nftContractAddress: contract address of the to be auctioned off NFT.
params.nftTokenId: the according Token ID of the NFT

endAuction().custom:emits: RevealBiddingAddresses a list of all L1 bidding addresses in plain text
endAuction().details: Pretty expensive, as it calls the oracle to fetch the balance of every bidding address one by one.Refer to README "2. Poor Scalability" of section "Limitations and Simplifications"

params._l1Addresses: all L1 bidding addresses (to be registered onchain).
params._winnerL1: L1 bidding address of the winner.
params._winningBid: balance of the winning bid at the blockheight when the auction ended = Bid.

getBiddingAddress().custom:confidential-input: a randomly created 32 byte key to be used for encryption.
getBiddingAddress().custom:emits: EncBiddingAddress(Suave sender address, L1 bidding address encrypted in bytes).
getBiddingAddress().details: If the caller has no bidding address so far, create a new bidding address and/else emit it in an encrypted fashion.Assumes the secret key is freshly generated and kept confidential by the sender.This method can be called even before the start & after the end of an auction.

refundNFT(address).details: calls the oracle to transfer the NFT.

params.returnAddressL1: L1 address where the NFT is to be sent to.

setUpAuction().details: The contract is the only entity in control of this address.Only confidentially callable by the auctioneer. Idempotent operation.

params._nftHoldingAddress: the address where the NFT must be sent to.
params.keyRecord: contains the Suave Data ID to lookup the private key in the Confidential Storage.

startAuction().details: Only confidentially callable by the auctioneer. Can only be called if the auction has not started yet.Calls the oracle to check if the NFT is at the nftHoldingAddress. Also checks if the end time has already passed.

backOutBid(address).notice: Until 15 minutes before the auction ends, a bidder is allowed to back out and reclaim the bid.

claim(address).notice: Central method for all to claim their valuables. Losers get their bid back;Winner gets the NFT; Auctioneer gets the winning bid.

constructor.notice: Creates the sealed auction contract to auction off a NFT.

endAuction().notice: Ends the auction by setting the winner. All bids being placed afterwards are invalid.

endAuctionOnchain(address,address,uint25.notice: Registers the winner and all L1 bidding addresses in the contract.If no bids or the minimal bidding amount is not kept, set the winner to the auctioneer

getBiddingAddress().notice: Get your personalized L1 bidding address to place your funds there (only decryptable by the caller).

getBiddingAddressOnchain(address,bytes16.notice: Registers the new bidding address on the contract. Increases bidder amount by one.

refundNFT(address).notice: Before the auction has started, the auctioneer has the option to claim the NFT back.

setUpAuction().notice: Generates a new nftHoldingAddress where the NFT is supposed to be sent to.

startAuction().notice: If the NFT was transferred beforehand, a call to this function starts the auction.
